{
  "video_id": "uq-6T6TAu74",
  "title": "Why some people are more altruistic than others | Abigail Marsh",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12760.0,
      "end_time": 14856.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s a man out there, somewhere,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 14880.0,
      "end_time": 17856.0,
      "text": "who looks a little bit like the actor Idris Elba,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 17880.0,
      "end_time": 20256.0,
      "text": "or at least he did 20 years ago."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 20280.0,
      "end_time": 22960.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t know anything else about him,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 22120.0,
      "end_time": 24160.0,
      "text": "except that he once saved my life"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 24400.0,
      "end_time": 25680.0,
      "text": "by putting his own life in danger."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 26600.0,
      "end_time": 31976.0,
      "text": "This man ran across four lanes of freeway traffic in the middle of the night"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 32000.0,
      "end_time": 33776.0,
      "text": "to bring me back to safety"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 33800.0,
      "end_time": 36575.0,
      "text": "after a car accident that could have killed me."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 36600.0,
      "end_time": 39256.0,
      "text": "And the whole thing left me really shaken up, obviously,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 39280.0,
      "end_time": 43256.0,
      "text": "but it also left me with this kind of burning, gnawing need"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 43280.0,
      "end_time": 44920.0,
      "text": "to understand why he did it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 45760.0,
      "end_time": 48536.0,
      "text": "what forces within him caused him to make the choice"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 48560.0,
      "end_time": 50416.0,
      "text": "that I owe my life to,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 50440.0,
      "end_time": 54560.0,
      "text": "to risk his own life to save the life of a stranger?"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 54800.0,
      "end_time": 59120.0,
      "text": "In other words, what are the causes of his or anybody else&#39;s capacity for altruism?"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 59840.0,
      "end_time": 61856.0,
      "text": "But first let me tell you what happened."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 61880.0,
      "end_time": 63336.0,
      "text": "That night, I was 19 years old"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 63360.0,
      "end_time": 65736.0,
      "text": "and driving back to my home in Tacoma, Washington,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 65760.0,
      "end_time": 67576.0,
      "text": "down the Interstate 5 freeway,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 67600.0,
      "end_time": 70136.0,
      "text": "when a little dog darted out in front of my car."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 70160.0,
      "end_time": 72496.0,
      "text": "And I did exactly what you&#39;re not supposed to do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 72520.0,
      "end_time": 73880.0,
      "text": "which is swerve to avoid it."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 74480.0,
      "end_time": 76920.0,
      "text": "And I discovered why you&#39;re not supposed to do that."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 77319.0,
      "end_time": 79560.0,
      "text": "I hit the dog anyways,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 79800.0,
      "end_time": 81696.0,
      "text": "and that sent the car into a fishtail,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 81720.0,
      "end_time": 84295.0,
      "text": "and then a spin across the freeway,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 84320.0,
      "end_time": 87895.0,
      "text": "until finally it wound up in the fast lane of the freeway"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 87920.0,
      "end_time": 90856.0,
      "text": "faced backwards into oncoming traffic"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 90880.0,
      "end_time": 92240.0,
      "text": "and then the engine died."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 93480.0,
      "end_time": 97400.0,
      "text": "And I was sure in that moment that I was about to die too,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 97880.0,
      "end_time": 99950.0,
      "text": "but I didn&#39;t"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 99120.0,
      "end_time": 101856.0,
      "text": "because of the actions of that one brave man"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 101880.0,
      "end_time": 103375.0,
      "text": "who must have made the decision"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 103400.0,
      "end_time": 106416.0,
      "text": "within a fraction of a second of seeing my stranded car"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 106440.0,
      "end_time": 110696.0,
      "text": "to pull over and run across four lanes of freeway traffic"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 110720.0,
      "end_time": 112656.0,
      "text": "in the dark"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 112680.0,
      "end_time": 114656.0,
      "text": "to save my life."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 114680.0,
      "end_time": 117576.0,
      "text": "And then after he got my car working again"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 117600.0,
      "end_time": 121216.0,
      "text": "and got me back to safety and made sure I was going to be all right,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 121240.0,
      "end_time": 122776.0,
      "text": "he drove off again."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 122800.0,
      "end_time": 125136.0,
      "text": "He never even told me his name,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 125160.0,
      "end_time": 127320.0,
      "text": "and I&#39;m pretty sure I forgot to say thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 128440.0,
      "end_time": 130376.0,
      "text": "So before I go any further,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 130400.0,
      "end_time": 131856.0,
      "text": "I really want to take a moment"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 131880.0,
      "end_time": 134680.0,
      "text": "to stop and say thank you to that stranger."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 135280.0,
      "end_time": 137000.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 142919.0,
      "end_time": 144136.0,
      "text": "I tell you all of this"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 144160.0,
      "end_time": 148376.0,
      "text": "because the events of that night changed the course of my life to some degree."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 148400.0,
      "end_time": 150160.0,
      "text": "I became a psychology researcher,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 150400.0,
      "end_time": 154816.0,
      "text": "and I&#39;ve devoted my work to understanding the human capacity to care for others."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 154840.0,
      "end_time": 157176.0,
      "text": "Where does it come from, and how does it develop,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 157200.0,
      "end_time": 159440.0,
      "text": "and what are the extreme forms that it can take?"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 160120.0,
      "end_time": 163296.0,
      "text": "These questions are really important to understanding basic aspects"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 163320.0,
      "end_time": 164560.0,
      "text": "of human social nature."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 165320.0,
      "end_time": 167416.0,
      "text": "A lot of people, and this includes everybody"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 167440.0,
      "end_time": 170335.0,
      "text": "from philosophers and economists to ordinary people"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 170360.0,
      "end_time": 173616.0,
      "text": "believe that human nature is fundamentally selfish,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 173640.0,
      "end_time": 177815.0,
      "text": "that we&#39;re only ever really motivated by our own welfare."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 177840.0,
      "end_time": 182136.0,
      "text": "But if that&#39;s true, why do some people, like the stranger who rescued me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 182160.0,
      "end_time": 184656.0,
      "text": "do selfless things, like helping other people"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 184680.0,
      "end_time": 187120.0,
      "text": "at enormous risk and cost to themselves?"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 187880.0,
      "end_time": 189176.0,
      "text": "Answering this question"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 189200.0,
      "end_time": 193296.0,
      "text": "requires exploring the roots of extraordinary acts of altruism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 193320.0,
      "end_time": 195696.0,
      "text": "and what might make people who engage in such acts"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 195720.0,
      "end_time": 197576.0,
      "text": "different than other people."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 197600.0,
      "end_time": 200680.0,
      "text": "But until recently, very little work on this topic had been done."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 201920.0,
      "end_time": 203736.0,
      "text": "The actions of the man who rescued me"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 203760.0,
      "end_time": 206736.0,
      "text": "meet the most stringent definition of altruism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 206760.0,
      "end_time": 209376.0,
      "text": "which is a voluntary, costly behavior"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 209400.0,
      "end_time": 211840.0,
      "text": "motivated by the desire to help another individual."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 212640.0,
      "end_time": 215760.0,
      "text": "So it&#39;s a selfless act intended to benefit only the other."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 216560.0,
      "end_time": 219120.0,
      "text": "What could possibly explain an action like that?"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 220120.0,
      "end_time": 222560.0,
      "text": "One answer is compassion, obviously,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 222800.0,
      "end_time": 223880.0,
      "text": "which is a key driver of altruism."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 224520.0,
      "end_time": 226136.0,
      "text": "But then the question becomes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 226160.0,
      "end_time": 228920.0,
      "text": "why do some people seem to have more of it than others?"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 230120.0,
      "end_time": 234160.0,
      "text": "And the answer may be that the brains of highly altruistic people"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 234400.0,
      "end_time": 236239.0,
      "text": "are different in fundamental ways."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 237120.0,
      "end_time": 239160.0,
      "text": "But to figure out how,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 239400.0,
      "end_time": 241160.0,
      "text": "I actually started from the opposite end,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 242160.0,
      "end_time": 243359.0,
      "text": "with psychopaths."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 244680.0,
      "end_time": 247776.0,
      "text": "A common approach to understanding basic aspects of human nature,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 247800.0,
      "end_time": 249816.0,
      "text": "like the desire to help other people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 249840.0,
      "end_time": 252976.0,
      "text": "is to study people in whom that desire is missing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 253000.0,
      "end_time": 255120.0,
      "text": "and psychopaths are exactly such a group."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 256200.0,
      "end_time": 258575.0,
      "text": "Psychopathy is a developmental disorder"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 258600.00000000003,
      "end_time": 260696.00000000003,
      "text": "with strongly genetic origins,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 260720.00000000003,
      "end_time": 263616.0,
      "text": "and it results in a personality that&#39;s cold and uncaring"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 263640.0,
      "end_time": 267164.0,
      "text": "and a tendency to engage in antisocial and sometimes very violent behavior."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 268400.0,
      "end_time": 271296.0,
      "text": "Once my colleagues and I at the National Institute of Mental Health"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 271320.0,
      "end_time": 273935.0,
      "text": "conducted some of the first ever brain imaging research"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 273959.0,
      "end_time": 276960.0,
      "text": "of psychopathic adolescents,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 276120.0,
      "end_time": 278976.0,
      "text": "and our findings, and the findings of other researchers now,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 279000.0,
      "end_time": 281296.0,
      "text": "have shown that people who are psychopathic"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 281320.0,
      "end_time": 284240.0,
      "text": "pretty reliably exhibit three characteristics."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 285160.0,
      "end_time": 289776.0,
      "text": "First, although they&#39;re not generally insensitive to other people&#39;s emotions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 289800.0,
      "end_time": 293576.0,
      "text": "they are insensitive to signs that other people are in distress."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 293600.0,
      "end_time": 294816.0,
      "text": "And in particular,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 294840.0,
      "end_time": 298736.0,
      "text": "they have difficulty recognizing fearful facial expressions like this one."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 298760.0,
      "end_time": 302456.0,
      "text": "And fearful expressions convey urgent need and emotional distress,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 302480.0,
      "end_time": 305960.0,
      "text": "and they usually elicit compassion and a desire to help"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 305120.0,
      "end_time": 306376.0,
      "text": "in people who see them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 306400.0,
      "end_time": 309960.0,
      "text": "so it makes sense that people who tend to lack compassion"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 309120.0,
      "end_time": 311240.0,
      "text": "also tend to be insensitive to these cues."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 312520.0,
      "end_time": 313736.0,
      "text": "The part of the brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 313760.0,
      "end_time": 316656.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s the most important for recognizing fearful expressions"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 316680.0,
      "end_time": 317936.0,
      "text": "is called the amygdala."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 317960.0,
      "end_time": 321376.0,
      "text": "There are very rare cases of people who lack amygdalas completely,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 321400.0,
      "end_time": 325256.0,
      "text": "and they&#39;re profoundly impaired in recognizing fearful expressions."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 325280.0,
      "end_time": 327655.0,
      "text": "And whereas healthy adults and children"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 327680.0,
      "end_time": 330296.0,
      "text": "usually show big spikes in amygdala activity"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 330320.0,
      "end_time": 332456.0,
      "text": "when they look at fearful expressions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 332480.0,
      "end_time": 335616.0,
      "text": "psychopaths&#39; amygdalas are underreactive to these expressions."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 335640.0,
      "end_time": 337296.0,
      "text": "Sometimes they don&#39;t react at all,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 337320.0,
      "end_time": 339940.0,
      "text": "which may be why they have trouble detecting these cues."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 341240.0,
      "end_time": 344376.0,
      "text": "Finally, psychopaths&#39; amygdalas are smaller than average"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 344400.0,
      "end_time": 346000.0,
      "text": "by about 18 or 20 percent."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 346920.0,
      "end_time": 350736.0,
      "text": "So all of these findings are reliable and robust,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 350760.0,
      "end_time": 352216.0,
      "text": "and they&#39;re very interesting."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 352240.0,
      "end_time": 353896.0,
      "text": "But remember that my main interest"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 353920.0,
      "end_time": 357456.0,
      "text": "is not understanding why people don&#39;t care about others."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 357480.0,
      "end_time": 359400.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s understanding why they do."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 359880.0,
      "end_time": 362176.0,
      "text": "So the real question is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 362200.0,
      "end_time": 364455.0,
      "text": "could extraordinary altruism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 364480.0,
      "end_time": 366696.0,
      "text": "which is the opposite of psychopathy"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 366720.0,
      "end_time": 370136.0,
      "text": "in terms of compassion and the desire to help other people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 370160.0,
      "end_time": 374176.0,
      "text": "emerge from a brain that is also the opposite of psychopathy?"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 374200.0,
      "end_time": 376440.0,
      "text": "A sort of antipsychopathic brain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 377880.0,
      "end_time": 380976.0,
      "text": "better able to recognize other people&#39;s fear,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 381000.0,
      "end_time": 383416.0,
      "text": "an amygdala that&#39;s more reactive to this expression"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 383440.0,
      "end_time": 385280.0,
      "text": "and maybe larger than average as well?"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 385920.0,
      "end_time": 387936.0,
      "text": "As my research has now shown,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 387960.0,
      "end_time": 389416.0,
      "text": "all three things are true."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 389440.0,
      "end_time": 390695.0,
      "text": "And we discovered this"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 390720.0,
      "end_time": 393736.0,
      "text": "by testing a population of truly extraordinary altruists."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 393760.0,
      "end_time": 396416.0,
      "text": "These are people who have given one of their own kidneys"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 396440.0,
      "end_time": 397640.0,
      "text": "to a complete stranger."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 398600.0,
      "end_time": 401696.0,
      "text": "So these are people who have volunteered to undergo major surgery"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 401720.0,
      "end_time": 404336.0,
      "text": "so that one of their own healthy kidneys can be removed"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 404360.0,
      "end_time": 406416.0,
      "text": "and transplanted into a very ill stranger"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 406440.0,
      "end_time": 408480.0,
      "text": "that they&#39;ve never met and may never meet."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 409400.0,
      "end_time": 411840.0,
      "text": "\"Why would anybody do this?\" is a very common question."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 412520.0,
      "end_time": 413895.0,
      "text": "And the answer may be"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 413920.0,
      "end_time": 416176.0,
      "text": "that the brains of these extraordinary altruists"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 416200.0,
      "end_time": 418000.0,
      "text": "have certain special characteristics."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 419400.0,
      "end_time": 422256.0,
      "text": "They are better at recognizing other people&#39;s fear."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 422280.0,
      "end_time": 425695.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re literally better at detecting when somebody else is in distress."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 425720.0,
      "end_time": 430376.0,
      "text": "This may be in part because their amygdala is more reactive to these expressions."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 430400.0,
      "end_time": 433335.0,
      "text": "And remember, this is the same part of the brain that we found"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 433360.0,
      "end_time": 435696.0,
      "text": "was underreactive in people who are psychopathic."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 435720.0,
      "end_time": 438616.0,
      "text": "And finally, their amygdalas are larger than average as well,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 438640.0,
      "end_time": 439856.0,
      "text": "by about eight percent."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 439880.0,
      "end_time": 441616.0,
      "text": "So together, what these data suggest"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 441640.0,
      "end_time": 445256.0,
      "text": "is the existence of something like a caring continuum in the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 445280.0,
      "end_time": 448816.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s anchored at the one end by people who are highly psychopathic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 448840.0,
      "end_time": 451335.0,
      "text": "and at the other by people who are very compassionate"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 451360.0,
      "end_time": 453280.0,
      "text": "and driven to acts of extreme altruism."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 454760.0,
      "end_time": 458695.0,
      "text": "But I should add that what makes extraordinary altruists so different"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 458720.0,
      "end_time": 461416.0,
      "text": "is not just that they&#39;re more compassionate than average."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 461440.0,
      "end_time": 462656.0,
      "text": "They are,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 462680.0,
      "end_time": 464576.0,
      "text": "but what&#39;s even more unusual about them"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 464600.0,
      "end_time": 466696.0,
      "text": "is that they&#39;re compassionate and altruistic"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 466720.0,
      "end_time": 469656.0,
      "text": "not just towards people who are in their own innermost circle"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 469680.0,
      "end_time": 471656.0,
      "text": "of friends and family. Right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 471680.0,
      "end_time": 474936.0,
      "text": "Because to have compassion for people that you love and identify with"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 474960.0,
      "end_time": 477159.0,
      "text": "is not extraordinary."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 478400.0,
      "end_time": 482216.0,
      "text": "Truly extraordinary altruists&#39; compassion extends way beyond that circle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 482240.0,
      "end_time": 484456.0,
      "text": "even beyond their wider circle of acquaintances"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 484480.0,
      "end_time": 487416.0,
      "text": "to people who are outside their social circle altogether,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 487440.0,
      "end_time": 488976.0,
      "text": "total strangers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 489000.0,
      "end_time": 490600.0,
      "text": "just like the man who rescued me."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 491960.0,
      "end_time": 495455.0,
      "text": "And I&#39;ve had the opportunity now to ask a lot of altruistic kidney donors"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 495480.0,
      "end_time": 499856.0,
      "text": "how it is that they manage to generate such a wide circle of compassion"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 499880.0,
      "end_time": 503216.0,
      "text": "that they were willing to give a complete stranger their kidney."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 503240.0,
      "end_time": 506736.0,
      "text": "And I found it&#39;s a really difficult question for them to answer."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 506760.0,
      "end_time": 510816.0,
      "text": "I say, \"How is it that you&#39;re willing to do this thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 510840.0,
      "end_time": 512816.0,
      "text": "when so many other people don&#39;t?"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 512840.00000000006,
      "end_time": 515256.00000000006,
      "text": "You&#39;re one of fewer than 2,000 Americans"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 515280.0,
      "end_time": 517895.0,
      "text": "who has ever given a kidney to a stranger."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 517919.0,
      "end_time": 519760.0,
      "text": "What is it that makes you so special?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 520400.0,
      "end_time": 521679.0,
      "text": "And what do they say?"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 523400.0,
      "end_time": 525319.0,
      "text": "They say, \"Nothing."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 526200.0,
      "end_time": 527976.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s nothing special about me."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 528000.0,
      "end_time": 529799.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m just the same as everybody else.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 531200.0,
      "end_time": 534296.0,
      "text": "And I think that&#39;s actually a really telling answer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 534320.0,
      "end_time": 538160.0,
      "text": "because it suggests that the circles of these altruists don&#39;t look like this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 539240.0,
      "end_time": 541216.0,
      "text": "they look more like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 541240.0,
      "end_time": 542480.0,
      "text": "They have no center."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 543320.0,
      "end_time": 545736.0,
      "text": "These altruists literally don&#39;t think of themselves"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 545760.0,
      "end_time": 548160.0,
      "text": "as being at the center of anything,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 548400.0,
      "end_time": 551000.0,
      "text": "as being better or more inherently important than anybody else."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 552000.0,
      "end_time": 555216.0,
      "text": "When I asked one altruist why donating her kidney made sense to her,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 555240.0,
      "end_time": 557960.0,
      "text": "she said, \"Because it&#39;s not about me.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 559400.0,
      "end_time": 560776.0,
      "text": "Another said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 560800.0,
      "end_time": 563550.0,
      "text": "\"I&#39;m not different. I&#39;m not unique."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 563800.0,
      "end_time": 566416.0,
      "text": "Your study here is going to find out that I&#39;m just the same as you.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 566440.0,
      "end_time": 570536.0,
      "text": "I think the best description for this amazing lack of self-centeredness"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 570560.0,
      "end_time": 572415.0,
      "text": "is humility,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 572440.0,
      "end_time": 575536.0,
      "text": "which is that quality that in the words of St. Augustine"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 575560.0,
      "end_time": 577790.0,
      "text": "makes men as angels."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 578120.0,
      "end_time": 579816.0,
      "text": "And why is that?"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 579840.0,
      "end_time": 582616.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s because if there&#39;s no center of your circle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 582640.0,
      "end_time": 585175.0,
      "text": "there can be no inner rings or outer rings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 585200.0,
      "end_time": 588960.0,
      "text": "nobody who is more or less worthy of your care and compassion"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 588120.0,
      "end_time": 589320.0,
      "text": "than anybody else."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 589920.0,
      "end_time": 593415.0,
      "text": "And I think that this is what really distinguishes extraordinary altruists"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 593440.0,
      "end_time": 594680.0,
      "text": "from the average person."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 595400.0,
      "end_time": 598976.0,
      "text": "But I also think that this is a view of the world that&#39;s attainable by many"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 599000.0,
      "end_time": 600976.0,
      "text": "and maybe even most people."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 601000.0,
      "end_time": 603256.0,
      "text": "And I think this because at the societal level,"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 603280.0,
      "end_time": 607000.0,
      "text": "expansions of altruism and compassion are already happening everywhere."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 607920.0,
      "end_time": 610376.0,
      "text": "The psychologist Steven Pinker and others have shown"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 610400.0,
      "end_time": 613656.0,
      "text": "that all around the world people are becoming less and less accepting"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 613680.0,
      "end_time": 616136.0,
      "text": "of suffering in ever-widening circles of others,"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 616160.0,
      "end_time": 619216.0,
      "text": "which has led to declines of all kinds of cruelty and violence,"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 619240.0,
      "end_time": 622760.0,
      "text": "from animal abuse to domestic violence to capital punishment."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 623480.0,
      "end_time": 626296.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s led to increases in all kinds of altruism."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 626320.0,
      "end_time": 629416.0,
      "text": "A hundred years ago, people would have thought it was ludicrous"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 629440.0,
      "end_time": 630936.0,
      "text": "how normal and ordinary it is"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 630960.0,
      "end_time": 634256.0,
      "text": "for people to donate their blood and bone marrow"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 634280.0,
      "end_time": 635920.0,
      "text": "to complete strangers today."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 636720.0,
      "end_time": 638816.0,
      "text": "Is it possible that a hundred years from now"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 638840.0,
      "end_time": 641416.0,
      "text": "people will think that donating a kidney to a stranger"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 641440.0,
      "end_time": 642896.0,
      "text": "is just as normal and ordinary"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 642920.0,
      "end_time": 645935.0,
      "text": "as we think donating blood and bone marrow is today?"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 645960.0,
      "end_time": 647160.0,
      "text": "Maybe."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 647800.0,
      "end_time": 650695.0,
      "text": "So what&#39;s at the root of all these amazing changes?"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 650720.0,
      "end_time": 652496.0,
      "text": "In part it seems to be"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 652520.0,
      "end_time": 655720.0,
      "text": "increases in wealth and standards of living."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 656600.0,
      "end_time": 659336.0,
      "text": "As societies become wealthier and better off,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 659360.0,
      "end_time": 661976.0,
      "text": "people seem to turn their focus of attention outward,"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 662000.0,
      "end_time": 665856.0,
      "text": "and as a result, all kinds of altruism towards strangers increases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 665880.0,
      "end_time": 670600.0,
      "text": "from volunteering to charitable donations and even altruistic kidney donations."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 671440.0,
      "end_time": 674416.0,
      "text": "But all of these changes also yield"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 674440.0,
      "end_time": 677656.0,
      "text": "a strange and paradoxical result,"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 677680.0,
      "end_time": 681215.0,
      "text": "which is that even as the world is becoming a better and more humane place,"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 681240.0,
      "end_time": 682456.0,
      "text": "which it is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 682480.0,
      "end_time": 685176.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s a very common perception that it&#39;s becoming worse"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 685200.0,
      "end_time": 687240.0,
      "text": "and more cruel, which it&#39;s not."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 688800.0,
      "end_time": 689896.0,
      "text": "And I don&#39;t know exactly why this is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 689920.0,
      "end_time": 693496.0,
      "text": "but I think it may be that we now just know so much more"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 693520.0,
      "end_time": 696696.0,
      "text": "about the suffering of strangers in distant places,"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 696720.0,
      "end_time": 699136.0,
      "text": "and so we now care a lot more"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 699160.0,
      "end_time": 701360.0,
      "text": "about the suffering of those distant strangers."
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 702240.0,
      "end_time": 705936.0,
      "text": "But what&#39;s clear is the kinds of changes we&#39;re seeing show"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 705960.0,
      "end_time": 708416.0,
      "text": "that the roots of altruism and compassion"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 708440.0,
      "end_time": 711456.0,
      "text": "are just as much a part of human nature as cruelty and violence,"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 711480.0,
      "end_time": 713176.0,
      "text": "maybe even more so,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 713200.0,
      "end_time": 717256.0,
      "text": "and while some people do seem to be inherently more sensitive"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 717280.0,
      "end_time": 719376.0,
      "text": "to the suffering of distant others,"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 719400.0,
      "end_time": 722175.0,
      "text": "I really believe that the ability to remove oneself"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 722200.0,
      "end_time": 723976.0,
      "text": "from the center of the circle"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 724000.0,
      "end_time": 728560.0,
      "text": "and expand the circle of compassion outward to include even strangers"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 728800.0,
      "end_time": 730880.0,
      "text": "is within reach for almost everyone."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 732800.0,
      "end_time": 733296.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 733320.0,
      "end_time": 740898.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}